mbers of the New\nYork Cotton Exchange on today's govern\nment report Is 13.61S.000.\nThere will be a government report Is\nsued next Wednesday on acreage and\ncondition of winter wheat and rje.\nThe statement of earnings submitted\nto the stock exchange by the United\nStates Itubber Company In connection\nwith Its application to list additional\nfirst preferred stock bhould be gratifying\nto the shareholders. Not only did the\ncompany hae a surplus of Sl.3tr3.MS over\nInterest and dividend requirements for\nthe period ended June 20 last, but the\nestimated surplus for the next three\nmonths, or up to September 30, was JW7.\nS5t N. L. Carpenter Co. The balance of\nthe market Is breaking away from New\nHaven and we believe that many of the\nactive -issues are a purchase. Wc favor\nUnion. Heading, and Utah Copper. The\nmarket may hesitate at times, as we\nhave liquidation in some special Issues,\nbut for the long pull we believe stocks\nmentioned will show a satisfactory pront\nin a reasonable time.\nS B. Chapln Co. to IV. B. Hlbbs\nle passage of the New Haven divi\ndend, which was conldered necessary by\nthe directors in the best Interests of the\nstockholders as well as to conserve those\nof the bondholders, was not allowed tc\nupset the market. There were good sup\nporting orders In all the standard rail\nroad and industrial stocks at the open.\nIng and these held bear raids in check\nand restricted liquidation.\n\"Aside from New .aven, the only really\nweak features were American Telephone\nand Telegraph and l'ennsylvanla. Kach\ndeclined to a maximum of 3 points from\njeoterdayVi closing.\n\"The liquidation In New Haven was of\na general character fcrclng Its price down\nto 671-S. The heavy speculative short\ninterest in the stock was covering on\nthis break and this helped to sustain\nIts price during the day with no dlvl\ndend now In sight for the stock for i\nlong time and further scattering liquida\ntion likely. Its price should ultimate) set\ntle around CO.\n\"It looks a though the general mar'cet\nwill now continue merely In a trading\nposition ror only moderate rallies.\"\nHarrlman Co Irregular recovery is\nexpected In stocks. Shrewd operators are\nhedging by purchasing the leading rail\nroad Issues whose margins of safety In\nearnings are reasonably largo and sell-\ning Industrial stocks that have been un\nder suspicion on various kinds for some\ntime. Investment will be found to ex\npand on a much larger scale In case of\nattacks on price for Investigations show\nthe presence of orders to buy at reces\nsions. These orders -have already been\nplaced In many western railroad stocks.\nIt seems to be a very strongly fixed\nopinion that the rajlroads will benefit\nirom uie lanrr, get nigner freight rates.\nsecure material cheaper and find a labor\nreadjustment Curing the course of the\nnext rew months. Heading is reported In\nposition to advance sharply. Information\nchannels are favorable to it. New lisv.n\nIs said to be In a final drive to shake\nout holders. The buying of Union Pacific\nanu boutnern raclnc la reported of high\nInside class. Steel, American Copper pre\nferred and New York Central are said to\nDe neaviiy oversold.\nrew York Financial Bureau to tv. -n\nHlbbs Irregular recovery Is expected In\nstocks. Shrewd operators are hedging\nuy purenasmg me leading railroad Is\nsues whose margins of safety In earnings\nare reasonably large, and selling indus\ntrial stocKs that- have been under sus\nplclon of variousjclnds fo'r some tim\nIt seems to be a very stronslv nieri\nopinion that the railroads will benefit\nirom uie tanrr, get nigner freight rates.\nt-ecure material cheaper, and find a labor\nreadjustment during the course of the\nnext iew months.\nReading Is reported In position to ad\nVance sharply\nInformation channels are favorable to\nNew Haven Is said to be in a final\ndrive to shako out holders.\nBuying of Union and Southern Pacific\nis reported 01 nign inside class.\nAtchison Is Bald ito be 'well taken.\nThe Traction issues are well bought\ne-leel. Amalgamated, and New York\nv-entrai are said to De heavily oversold.\n\"Experts In European finance now hold\nthat Americaa -securities of worth are\npractically at Intrinsic levels.\" says a\nprivate cable from London:\nE. C. Randolph to \"vV B. Hlbbs i\nCo. The opening Vas rather reran rirn hi.\nIn that material advances were msde in\nmany Issues 1n\" the face of a verv whan.\nbreak In New Haven. There was a \"large\nand excited crowd around the New Haven\npoet uong Before the jsxenange opened,\nand sales were made at the start 1 1-2\npoints apartr the Urst transaction being\niwvnira m o,iav snares bl ra 1-3 to, qc\nI d j jsas, a.\nKJnst -TlS- at the close- yesterday, m.\nJ41tolTgh1tAeTeswas!rKmietfIevrtetruicy In\nra rest of tne market at the start, U-\nmost Immediately prices were bid up\n\"harply. This was most noticeable In\nHtrcL, which opened at &61-8, and within a\new minutes ran up to 61 1-, witn corres-\nPonding strength In Union. Reading, and\nother leading speculative Issues. Stock:\nM freely supplied on the rise, however,\nand prices soon reacted again, and the\ntone became heavy. New Haven con\ntinued 'under pressure, selling down be\nfore 12 o'clock below the lowest price,\ntouched at the opening. Sympathetic\nweakness affneted American Telephone.\nThroughout the general list dealings con\ntinued largely In the' hands '-ot profes\nsionals, and the market as a whole has\nsnown but little tendency to break out\nof Its rut. It was estimated that the\nearnings of the various steel companies\nwas smaller In November than at any\nuuie since 1905.\nNEW YORK PRODUCE\nNc Tork. Dee. 1L MILLFEsrD Firmer: mod\nerate deaunga. gpring bran. In 100-poond sacks,\n24-60; standard middling, SJ0; Weatern red dog.\n2.B; \"Inter wheat, in 100-poond sacks, to arrlte.\n36.70; city bran. In bulk. SJ0; Argentine bran, to\nsrriTe. nominal.\nBYE FLOUn-Steadj: business Is limited. Good\nto choice, at Xa3.95. in barrets.\nCO UNHEAL